00:52:54.739 --> 00:53:00.130
during that period. You start seeing a shift
because of the IBM Anti-trust case in the

00:53:00.130 --> 00:53:10.039
late '60's and so IBM is forced to stop giving
the software away for free with the hardware.

00:53:10.039 --> 00:53:13.989
The beginnings of the software industry are
already developing in the '60's, but that

00:53:13.989 --> 00:53:19.849
really gives the main boost then in the 1960's,
ah, 1970's. I think it's no wonder that, you

00:53:19.849 --> 00:53:26.520
know someone like Bill Gates really helps
redefine the business model around software,

00:53:26.520 --> 00:53:35.730
in that his dad was a lawyer, not an engineer.
And, I mean, one could make the case that

00:53:35.730 --> 00:53:40.210
also that bringing a group of smart people
together and having them work on a singular

00:53:40.210 --> 00:53:47.549
project and then patenting the outcome is
an effective way of innovation as well. So,

00:53:47.549 --> 00:53:54.029
I guess both and, both ways of doing it are
both viable and we've seen it work, um, but

00:53:54.029 --> 00:53:58.549
open source isn't something new. Open source
was actually the way things were originally

00:53:58.549 --> 00:53:59.549
done.

